        <bioghist id="ref7">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>George L. Ferguson, of Elyria, Ohio, was a Sergeant First Class in the U.S. Army in 1918. While serving in France with the 306th Field Signal Battalion, 81st Division, A.E.F., Ferguson won the Distinguished Service Cross.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>The collections consists of letters written from George L. Ferguson while on active service with the American Expeditionary Force during and immediately following World War I in France and Scotland, to Julia Harvey Ingles of Dublin and Abingdon, Virginia. The letters are dated 1918 and 1919.</p>
        </scopecontent>
